# Licensing

Different parts of this repository are licensed under different terms, with
third-party components retaining their own upstream licenses.

## Source code — MIT License

The build tooling and software in this repository — including `Makefile`,
`setup.sh`, the Haskell sources under `tools/`, the formalization viewer
sources under `tools/formalization-viewer/` (excluding `vendor/`, see below),
the Python scripts, and the Lean sources — are licensed under the MIT License.
See [LICENSE-MIT](LICENSE-MIT).

## Written content — CC BY 4.0

The written mathematical content — the Markdown book sources, the TeX prose
and macros, figures, and the rendered PDF documents — is licensed under the
Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International License (CC BY 4.0).
See [LICENSE-CC-BY-4.0](LICENSE-CC-BY-4.0).

## Third-party components

Vendored third-party code under `tools/formalization-viewer/vendor/` is NOT
covered by the licenses above. Each component is redistributed under its own
upstream license. See
[tools/formalization-viewer/vendor/THIRD-PARTY-NOTICES.md](tools/formalization-viewer/vendor/THIRD-PARTY-NOTICES.md)
for the full list, versions, and license texts.
